  <title>Truco Uruguayo</title>
  <p>Truco Uruguayo uses a "Muestra" (similar to Vira). The logic for the strongest cards (Piezas) depends on the Muestra's suit.</p>
  
  <section id="piezas">
    <title>The Piezas</title>
    <p>The strongest cards are the Piezas of the Muestra suit (if they exist). They are ranked:</p>
    <list type="numbered">
        <item><p><strong>2 of the Muestra Suit</strong></p></item>
        <item><p><strong>4 of the Muestra Suit</strong></p></item>
        <item><p><strong>5 of the Muestra Suit</strong></p></item>
        <item><p><strong>11 (Jack) of the Muestra Suit</strong> (Perico)</p></item>
        <item><p><strong>10 (King) of the Muestra Suit</strong> (Perica)</p></item>
    </list>
    <p>Example: If Muestra is 2 of Spades:</p>
    <p>
        <media type="image" src="figures/2_of_spades.svg" width="60"/> <gui>Muestra</gui> ➔ 
        <media type="image" src="figures/2_of_spades.svg" width="60"/> <gui>Highest Pieza</gui>
    </p>
  </section>
</page>
